HEADWORD: White-livered
<hw>White"-liv`ered</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Having a pale
look; feeble; hence, cowardly; pusillanimous; dastardly.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> lily-livered.</syn>
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>They must not be milksops, nor <qex>white-livered</qex>
knights.</q> <rj><qau>Latimer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Whitely</ent>⟦br⟧
